text: Arizona's 26th Legislative District is one of 30 in the state, situated in Maricopa County. As of 2018 there are 34 precincts in the district, with a total registered voter population of 93,530. ==Political representation== The district is represented for the 2018–2019 Legislative Session in the State Senate by Juan Mendez (D, Tempe) and in the House of Representatives by Isela Blanc (D, Tempe) and Athena Salman (D, Tempe). ==References== Category:Maricopa County, Arizona Category:Arizona legislative districts
title: Arizona's 26th legislative district
